{"key":"post-10363383","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>10363383</id>\n<content>Exactly.&amp;nbsp; Normally, grains must either be cased or spawned to manure or another bulk substrate in order to produce fruits.&amp;nbsp; A few years ago, growers found that by mixing verm with grains, they'd fruit as if spawned to a bulk substrate.&amp;nbsp; My theory is that verm also has food for the mycelium, and not just moisture holding capacity(reservoir effect), but the idea is controversial and unproved.&amp;nbsp; I just toss it out here as something to ponder.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>10363426</next>\n<prev>10361941</prev>\n<first>10361763</first>\n<last>22978455</last>\n<when>1242744308</when>\n<utime>05/19/09 05:45 PM</utime>\n</post>"}